@page "/how-to"

<PageTitle>How To Use</PageTitle>

<h1>Iris Content Import — How to Use</h1>

<div class="mt-4">

    <h3>Step 1 — Prepare your localized content <span class="badge bg-secondary">Web App</span></h3>
    <p>Upload an .html email file to get started. The locale is parsed from the filename (e.g. <code>email_en-us.html</code> → en-US). You'll be able to edit the content and generate a .csv and .xlsx file for localization.</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Create your original .html content file. The subject line for the email needs to go into the <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> tag in the headers.</li>
        <li>Go to the web app's <strong>Localize</strong> tab and upload the .html file into the first section.</li>
        <li>Download the .csv or .xlsx strings file for localization.</li>
        <li>Fill in translations (or upload a multi-sheet .xlsx with one sheet per locale).</li>
        <li>Upload the translated file — localized .html files will be generated.</li>
    </ol>

    <hr />

    <h3>Step 2 — Export .xml from Iris Content <span class="badge bg-secondary">ICMS</span></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>In ICMS, create the content object you're going to work with using the <strong>IrisEmailTemplate</strong> content type. This will be under the InvariantCulture tab. Fill in the Subject content, PlainTextBody content, and HtmlBodyFormat content. <em>Note: Any content will do — can be as simple as "Test" in each.</em></li>
        <li>Save the file, check it in, and then right click on the file name and choose <strong>"Export for localization."</strong></li>
        <li>Save the .xml file to your desktop.</li>
    </ol>

    <hr />

    <h3>Step 3 — Generate the import package <span class="badge bg-secondary">Web App</span></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to the <strong>Iris Content Import</strong> page in the tool.</li>
        <li>Upload the .xml file from Step 2.</li>
        <li>The tool will show the content item name, ID, and existing variants.</li>
        <li>Select the source file that matches this content item from the dropdown.</li>
        <li>Review the list of locales that will be generated — <span class="badge bg-success">green</span> badges are new, <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">yellow</span> badges already exist in Iris.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>📦 Generate Import Package</strong>.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>⬇ Download .zip</strong>.</li>
        <li>
            Extract the downloaded .zip to a folder (e.g. <code>D:\ContentForImport\NewImportTest\</code>). The extracted folder will contain locale-named subfolders:
            <pre class="bg-light p-2 mt-2"><code>NewImportTest\
  fr-FR\
    NewImportTest_991667d0-...xml
  de-DE\
    NewImportTest_991667d0-...xml</code></pre>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <hr />

    <h3>Step 4 — Import into Iris Content <span class="badge bg-secondary">ICMS</span></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>In Iris Content, click on the <strong>"Import from Localization"</strong> link at the top of the page.</li>
        <li>Point it to the extracted folder from Step 3.</li>
        <li>Iris Content will read each subfolder name as the target locale and import the variant content.</li>
        <li>Double click the content object to verify localized versions have been imported.</li>
    </ol>

    <hr />

    <h3>Step 5 — Recreate InvariantCulture <span class="badge bg-secondary">ICMS</span></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Check out the content object.</li>
        <li>Delete the InvariantCulture content by clicking the red X.</li>
        <li>Recreate it by clicking <strong>"Add new"</strong> and selecting <strong>"Invariant Culture"</strong> from the Choose languages and locales section. Select <strong>Copy from</strong> one of the localized locales you imported in Step 4.</li>
    </ol>

    <hr />

    <h3>What the tool generates for each locale</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Subject</strong> — extracted from the <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> tag of the HTML</li>
        <li><strong>Plain text body</strong> — auto-generated from the HTML (no tags, links preserved inline)</li>
        <li><strong>HTML body</strong> — the full localized .html content</li>
    </ul>

</div>
